+## Local Web UI (non-Docker, optional)
+
+If the user wants the web UI without Docker, `hive setup` provisions the whole local mode in one idempotent command — preflight, bootstrap the deps Hive owns (qmd + the web bundle), install the daemon on the same binary and enroll the repo, and install + start the web service at `http://127.0.0.1:4567`:
+
+```bash
+"$hive_cmd" setup --json
+```
+
+Exit 0 (possibly with warnings) means local mode is ready; the warnings list exact fix commands for any missing/unauthenticated external agent CLI (`gh`, `claude`, `codex`) — do NOT install or authenticate those for the user, just report them. A non-zero exit is a hard blocker (Ruby too old, a refused non-loopback bind, or a web bundle that will not build). For the web service alone, `"$hive_cmd" web install` / `start` / `stop` / `status` mirror the daemon subcommands; bare `"$hive_cmd" web` always works in the foreground. The default bind is loopback; a non-loopback bind is refused unless a GitHub owner/device-flow is configured or `--unsafe` is passed. This does not affect the Docker/hivebox path.
+
 ## Initialize Project
 
