+## Binary consistency (local mode)
+
+`Hive::DaemonConsistency` verifies the installed unit's ExecStart binary
+matches the CLI's resolved binary (via `ServiceInstaller::Base#target_binary`,
+compared by realpath so symlinks don't false-positive) and, when a
+running-daemon version is known, that the daemon is not on stale code. It
+classifies `ok` / `drifted` / `stale` / `not_installed` / `unknown`
+(cannot-determine is `unknown`, never a false `drifted`). The web UI surfaces
+this via `DaemonHealthController` (`GET /daemon_health` JSON + an owner-gated
+`POST /daemon_health/repair` that re-runs `hive daemon install --force`).
+`hive setup` ([[commands/setup]]) uses the same install path so a drifted
+`/usr/bin/hive` unit is repaired onto the wrapper binary.
+
