diff --git a/wiki/commands/setup.md b/wiki/commands/setup.md
new file mode 100644
index 00000000..bd7f7685
--- /dev/null
+++ b/wiki/commands/setup.md
@@ -0,0 +1,68 @@
+---
+title: hive setup
+type: command
+source: lib/hive/commands/setup.rb, lib/hive/local_preflight.rb, lib/hive/web/bundle_installer.rb, lib/hive/qmd_bootstrap.rb, lib/hive/commands/web/service_installer.rb, lib/hive/daemon_consistency.rb
+created: 2026-07-10
+updated: 2026-07-10
+tags: [command, setup, web, daemon, local, hivebox]
+---
+
+**TLDR**: `hive setup` is the one-command orchestrator for **local (non-Docker)
+install/run mode**. It brings up the same pipeline the TUI and web UI share —
+against the user's real XDG/home Hive state (via [[dependencies|Hive::Paths]],
+no sandbox) — by sequencing: preflight → bootstrap Hive-owned deps → daemon
+install + project enroll → web install/start. The Docker/hivebox path
+([[web]]) is untouched and remains a supported alternative.
+
+## Pipeline
+
+`Hive::Commands::Setup#call` runs these steps, aggregating a `hive-setup.v1`
+JSON envelope (`--json`) or a bare-text checklist:
+
+1. **Bind gate** — resolve the effective web bind (`--bind` → `web.bind` →
+   `127.0.0.1`). A non-loopback bind is REFUSED before any mutation unless a
+   GitHub owner/device-flow is configured, `--unsafe` is passed, or the
+   `HIVE_WEB_ALLOW_PUBLIC_BIND` escape hatch is set (the hivebox supervisor
+   sets it). Same rule as the [[web]] run-time guard.
+2. **Preflight** (`Hive::LocalPreflight`) — verifies Ruby ≥ 3.4, git, tmux,
+   gh, claude, codex, node/npm, qmd, the `web/` Rails bundle, and the sqlite3
+   CLI. Ruby-too-old is the only hard stop (exit non-zero, no mutation). Every
+   other required gap is an actionable **warning** carrying the exact fix
+   command — Hive never installs or authenticates external agent CLIs.
+3. **Bootstrap Hive-owned deps** — `Hive::QmdBootstrap` (no-op when qmd
+   resolves; mirrors `install.sh install_qmd`) and `Hive::Web::BundleInstaller`
+   (`bundle install` + `db:prepare` in `web/`, idempotent, typed refusal when
+   `web/` is absent). A web bundle that will not install is a **blocking**
+   failure.
+4. **Daemon** — `hive daemon install` (same resolved binary as the CLI, via
+   `ServiceInstaller::Base#resolved_binary`) then `hive daemon enable <project>`
+   (defaults to the repo at cwd). Drift without `--force` is surfaced as a
+   warning, not a clobber. See [[daemon]] and `Hive::DaemonConsistency`.
+5. **Web** — `hive web install` + `hive web start` unless `--no-web-service`
+   (then it prints the foreground `hive web` command). See [[web]].
+
+## Exit codes
+
+- **0** — ready, or ready-with-warnings (missing/unauthenticated external
+  CLIs). Automation keeps going; the warnings list the exact fix commands.
+- **non-zero** — a hard-blocking failure: Ruby too old, a refused non-loopback
+  bind, or a web bundle that will not install. No partial mutation past the
+  failing gate.
+
+Re-running is idempotent: the underlying service installers no-op when the
+unit already matches and never overwrite hand-edited units without `--force`.
+
+## Flags
+
+`--bind` / `--port` (web bind, defaults `127.0.0.1:4567`), `--project NAME`
+(enroll target; defaults to the cwd repo), `--no-web-service` (print the
+foreground command instead of installing a service), `--unsafe` (allow a
+non-loopback bind without an auth/owner flow), `--json` (`hive-setup.v1`).
+
+## Boundaries
+
+`hive setup` does not install or authenticate `gh` / `claude` / `codex`, does
+not touch the Docker path, and does not redesign the auth model — it only
+gates when a public bind requires auth. Windows is out of scope. See
+[[commands/web]] for the managed service surface and [[commands/daemon]] for
+enrollment and binary-consistency repair.
