+  `web/` next to `lib/`), exports `SECRET_KEY_BASE` (derived from the same
+  persisted `Hive::Web::SessionSecret` file — sessions survive container
+  recreation), `HIVEBOX_ORIGIN`, and `HIVEBOX_STORAGE_DIR` (the solid-stack
+  sqlite files under `Hive::Paths.state_home/web-storage`), runs
+  `bin/rails db:prepare`, then execs `bin/rails server`. Outside the container
+  or a source checkout it exits 1 with guidance — the gem does not package the
+  Rails app (`test/unit/gemspec_test.rb` pins that).
+- **`hive web install [--force]`** — write + enable a platform-native managed
+  service (systemd-user `hive-web.service` on Linux, launchd
+  `local.hive-web.plist` on macOS) via
+  `Hive::Commands::Web::ServiceInstaller` — a third subclass of the shared
+  `ServiceInstaller::Base` pattern (alongside daemon and bot). ExecStart is the
+  resolved wrapper binary + `web`; a `--bind`/`--port` given at install time is
+  baked in. The web and daemon are **distinct services**, never merged.
+- **`hive web start` / `stop`** — drive `systemctl --user` / `launchctl`.
+  Absent a service manager, `start` prints the foreground command.
+- **`hive web status [--json]`** — `hive-web-status.v1`: `service_installed`,
+  `service_enabled`, `unit_path`, `running`, `platform`.
+
+### Non-loopback bind guard
+
+Loopback (the `127.0.0.1:4567` default) needs no auth. A **non-loopback bind is
+refused** unless (a) a GitHub owner/device-flow claim is configured
+(`web.github.owner`), (b) `--unsafe` is passed, or (c) the
+`HIVE_WEB_ALLOW_PUBLIC_BIND` env escape hatch is set. The hivebox
+`Hive::Web::Supervisor` sets that env so the Docker box (which binds `0.0.0.0`
+by design and gates access via the claim model) is unaffected. Allowed
+public binds without an owner still log a warning.
 
